{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was, of course, always in alphabetical order, so it was a great excitement kind of thing when they went through in alphabetical order and they got near to your letter kind of thing and then they passed your letter and you were not on the list.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This ?] [? was ?] obviously a great feeling of relief, relaxation kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we didn't actually hear them being called out, but we found pretty soon, because they were not in our barracks.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We found out that they were due for deportation next morning.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father tried, with his German connections and this [INAUDIBLE] connections and his British connections and all these sort of things, to prevent them being deported, but it didn't help.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So next morning, they were deported.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We all had to stay in our barracks in the morning, so we didn't see them [INAUDIBLE] leave.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nobody was allowed out at morning on Tuesday mornings, except the people that were being deported.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Until the train had left, nobody was outside.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, after the war.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't know anything then.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were for resettlement in the East.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But after the war, at the [INAUDIBLE], we found all the records because the Germans had been extremely meticulous-- both the Germans and the Dutch-- and both of them have records of everybody who went through Westerbork-- their date of birth, where they went, and when they died.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we found out that all four grandparents went to Sobibor, and all four grandparents were killed the day after they arrived.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In fact, from Westerbork, 34,000 people went to Sobibor. 19 survived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was far worse than Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In Auschwitz, 58,000 people went to Auschwitz from Westerbork and 800 survived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At Sobibor, nobody survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We've seen models of Sobibor and Treblinka.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
